{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_sierra_ver02/data/sn84026749/100492635/1908051101/0015.xml":{"full_text":"NEW YORK STOCKS\nSTART OUT HIGHER\nEE Ee\n\n\n\ni Ce ERA\nOld Leaders Give Prece\ndence to Minor Shares\u2014In\ndustrials Very Firm.\n\n\ni\n\n\nas os aR j EE.\nDAY'S GAINS\n\n\nGenera! Electric...... Sacesany sesuiein.\nNational BiSOUit......cconrrrnivsnnes HB\nConselidated $y\nNock\n2\n1\nChicsgo Gas............... RARE 1\nSeal em... 00 Eres rensirenee Bi\nSeal nf. se srusnaesrateey IB\nVirginia-Carolina Chemical. RR\nSteel Ca: 1\na\n\n\n\n\nJ\nJ a TRE SR Ce 15\ns\n\n\nCal anf FoOuNGry...ccovieu isis sens 3g\nI Re A SE 1\nER RRR RE RT i.\n Seeltar FETA STRUT RR A PRPS, 0a oh 1\nCn de Srr ate AR ss sve Rane 15\nAnaconda Ere rrwrhe reas reves 13%\nUnion FPaeific FT AOL, reg\nLL TE RE ARS I A A \u201c8\nBouthern Pacific... .....ccoivnvens bg\nTouisville ang Nashville... .vverers EA\nAtisanur: Pacifie cia erress Te\nNew York Ceniral.......... iverf penn 2\nAM ERI orc srrasssresnr rernr rns seep\nROSIE ISBN ices cine rssrertns Ts\nSouthern Raiiway veanias\nw\n\ni\n\ni\n\n1\n\nR 1 An\nEe ee le\n\n\n\n\n\n\ni\ni\n\n\nBouthern Pacifie ha. crssessrrereer 342\nAtlantic Coast LiNe...cciseerersnnss 98\n\ni\nHaltimore and Ohio....... sercsursane 1k\nCapadian Pacific .............c000n 1%\nChesapeake and -Ohio........ sesatan\nInterborough Metropolitan 1%\nKanes City Southern 5. 1s\nDelaware and Hugson............ I LY\nBig TARR ER h irene 8\nyr a\n\n\n\n\nSe oe Er\n\n\nNEW YORK, May 1L\u2014Stocks startad\nin a runaway with mucin enthusiasm\nand many advances in values. The suc\n\u2018ces of the different buli pools ln ad\nvaacing their specialties has given\nthem new courage, ana the bears. who\nhave !ost much of their 197 profits in\nfigliting the advance, have quit dis\ngustad, and while not willing to fol\nlow the lead of the bulls in their hur\nrah market, they are watching and\nwalting for the reaction that must\ncome, when they will break in and\nreip it along. The fact that the up\nward movement has been maintained\nrieadlly for several weeks incites the\nLope of public buying. The crops are\nvnquestionably forward, and from ail\ncactiens of the country comes the\npresage of an abundant harvest.\nI\nt\ni i 1\n\n\nj\nt\nnatin ru he.\nid\n\nJ\n\n\n\ni i\nI\n\nn\ni\nPailroad earnings are bad. but the\nru.iroads are beginning to master this\nhy reducing operating expenses, so that\nwhile gross earnings continue unsatis\nfactory. net earnings are showing some\nlinnrevement.\n4\nfp\n\n\n\n\nThe present bull movement snot\nbased on anvihing but manipulation,\nand that it shoula continue, in the face\nof uncertain political conditions, is a\ntribute to the master manipulators hat\nmay be extended into something se\n\ni\n\ni i\n\nPR TTT 3\nQuieter After Opening.\na\nAfter the getaway, the market came\nback to normal activity, profit taking\nteing responsible for material reactions\nhere and there. The feature of the\nearly rise was the display of strength\nin. minor stocks, like Atlantic Coast\nLine Chesapeake and Ohio, Norfolk and\nWestern, Louisville and Nashville, and\nRaltimore and Ohio. Some of the in\nJustrials also showed remarkable\nstrength.\n0\n\n\n\nf\n\nI\n\nJ op\u2014\nN\n\ni\nEE\ni a i di Lo St tt de th ie at a ie da a ad s\n\nJust why these minor stocks should ha\ninflated so quickly is one of tiie gu:Ss\nproblems of the Street. Aflantic Coast\nJ.ine, Chesapeake and Ohio, and some\nother stocks that \u2018had a world of ginger\ni]\nFIR seve 4 8\nIR\ni oa ame 4 H\ni H\nseid ae\nia them on the start this morning, have\nLeen more or lesg under the ban of late,\nand were considered to have some prob\nlems of interest to be solved. But they\nJumped, and in their jumping made good\n.caps. New York Central is another\nstock that seemed as if it would not\nie headed on the rise.\nTR ree\nAdi 1\nx i ....ociiiiiiis 1 i\n9 4\ni i\n\n\n\nH\nI _| ii\nIt is simply wonderful how these\nstocks that could scarcely be given away\na few weeks ago, when the Erie mat\nter was up for consideration, have in\ncreased in value\u2014nine-tenths on nerve\nand one-ienih an easy money.\nana\nA RE AY RA Prt AS REITINT 2 B00 mE GA NTA NS A ATAPI P51 j|\n\nF i i\nHS\n\nt i!\nFS\ne i\nAtlantic Coast Line started at 87, not\na fractional gain, but an anvance on\nthe initial saie of 13 points, and then it\nturned to 89. Somebody wanted it bad\nly to bid when it might bave been\nbought cheaper. There is a way of bid\nding stocks up, just as there is a way\nto sell them down.\n\ni\n\nBaltimore and Ohio sold at gain.\nCanadian Pacific added a point. Chesa\npeake and Ohie started a point higher,\nadded more, and fell a point. Dela\nware and Hudson 1% better. Great\nNorthern did not push forward as did\nthe stocks that are not worth half its\nprice. This may be surprising, other\ninan on tie theory that good stocks\nhave had their rise. Indeed, while the\nlittie fellows were booming Great\nNorthern sold down Union Pacific\nstarted a little better, and was off 15 a\nnoon. Louisville and Nashville gained\nto 110, and back to 109. New York Cen\nira! started higher on the first quota\ntion, going to 106%, and back to 106.\nNorthern Pacific acted like other good\nleadors\u2014iot vary well. Reading did the\n6niae, turning 136, and going back the\ngain and a lictle more. It was the same\nwih Southern Pacific and St Paul,\naftar a firm opening. Copper gained a\ni\n1 est\n\ni\n\nSint. Cotton Oil 3, Sugar 3, Consoli\nred Cas, 1, and General Electric an\nConeglicated Gas the same.\nWell into tie second hour of the after\nnoch the markot continued to quiet\ndown. whileithe high grade ralig Sera\ntied Lack to Saturday's closing or a\nI'tde below. The minor ralls continue\nto present a arm front. noi yielding. In\niho industrials the Steel advanced ig\nte 1 on the outside for the preferred.\nTha Intent of the manufaciurers to hold\ncontracts at high prices being torougle\nly urderstood. oe, Smelter, Ccepger,\nand Sugar were 3 to 1% higher.\nThe indications were favorable for a\ncontinuatica of these conditions,\n\n\n\nUp to the close the industrials held\nthelr adiances nicesy, and some of the\nmincr reils. The hig rails went off in\nvesterday's cios'ng, but in the late trad.\ning therc were some slight recoveries.\nThe market reiained its activity to the\nclose.\ni\n1\n\n\ni\n\nos]\nhw ao RAS shi b&b 4 bd\nrs\n\nhtt fil, 0 aa lh, an dB ten dR\nEISEMAN BROS,\nOutdtiars for Both Men axl Boys\n7in and E Streets.\n\nCorract Hering jor Boys\nhad cater to 0 VOURK MiaNe\u2014\nCur Furmenis are wade 13zht\nfis ne fares fault lossy\nBE\nSpecial line at $3.30 and $5.00.\nBE Ldd Lab AALAAA\nI cs\u201d Zh a ZR MR Ca hr RR GL Ca i a ah.\nh J\nThe Wonder of It!\n\nPRICES FOR TODAY ON\nNEW YORK EXCHANGE\ni i\n(Quotations furnished by W. B. Hibbs\nCo., bapkers and brokers, Hibbs Building,\n\n\nmembers New York Stock Exchange, Wash\nington \u00a3tock Exchange and Chicago Hoard of\nade\n\ni i i\nAmal. Ge 64g 62% 64\na 0 I eds saan 5 a 3\nEE  maa\u2014\u2014 nt ce\nTE 3\ni\nAm. Beet ar Co... 21 2% 21. Iu\nAm. Can Co., pfd.... 5 6 5 56\nAm. Car Foundry... 3%3% 31% 26% 37%\nAm, Car Foundry, pf. 9 WW om\nAm. Cotton OI! Co.... 28% 30 28% 30\nAm. 106 SeC......v 00s 23% 28% 23% 24%\nAmer, Locomotive. 50%, Gl; 508g 50%\nAmer, Smelting....... 3. 3% 0% eh\nAmer, Smelt., pf... 58 38 95 9\nAmer, Sugarl..........128% 129% 128 120.3\nAmer, Tob. pl........ 92 92 92 92h\nAnasonda .......os. cox 385% 40 3835 30%,\nAtch., Top. S. Fe.. Slig X17 Sli 82%\nA. 88 Fo opf.... 2 ai, 92 9g\nAtlantic Gea Line. 8815 50\nBalto Ohio...... XD wae NY\nBrook. Rpd. Tran..... 48% 57 475% 7s\nCanadian Pacific... 1585 1661; on 154\nCentral Leather $i% 0% 26% 20%\nChess Obde.......... 44 Wy 8\nChicago G. W..-v.:+ve 2\nM&S. Pi. 1545, 134% 133% 130%\n8\n\net i ENE\nSe\na 3) 4\ni i\nhk i. pt pb\n1\ni Dae\nI 1\n\nC. M. St P. a 152\nChicago N. W.......15\u00a2% 154%\nWI\nColorado F. 1....... XCOX& IN NN\nColorado Southern 30% 31% 30% 31%\nCol. Hock C. &i