ifth Ave.,, New York\nPER Nt i JEM BR TEV av Seve Bd EERETIR TRENT TRE SRA Ege CAT SA TOR PEAR LSC on ARR REE TIER RE em\nCh herd M ey 2 y\n4\nek i nll\n3 Sw,\nhil\nJ\na Ua SRR at uh Sei ah a a a a wale oo uh di LHR bt atti Seal\nTHE CURB MARKET.\nSTOCKS STRONG:\nTRACTIONS LEAD\nNational City Bank Trade\nUnder Way\u2014Gas Stock\nWas Slow.\nIt was a fairly active day on the local\nStock Exchange, with the feature a\nraise of 20 points in the bid price of\nNational City Bank stock, which at\nonce suggested a reswuption of nego\ntiations for sale, and this proved to be\nihe fact. The negotiations are well\nunder way.\nwashingion Railway, common, was\na~tive at 323% to 33, and the preferred\nwas strong at and 8215. Capital Trace\nticn was wanted and sold at 123%.\nGas. steady at 69%, this being a re\nduction of from last saie. The move\nment in it seems to have ceased for the\ntime being.\nMergenthaler was in good demand\nana higher at 18g and 105%.\nSE ereteial National Bank turned\nVe\nbonds were scarce and firm.\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES, MOXDAY. MAY 11, 1908.\nkJ\n\nQUOTATIONS FOR TODAY\nON WASHINGTON EXCHANGE\nWashington Gas 45, 9UU@ds.\nwashington Railway and Electric 4's,\n$1.0008r82%. 5\nCaphal Traction, 1@i23%, 2041233, 1\n124.\nWashington Railway and Electric,\ncommon, Wald, Hai, a@ili, UI,\nrds, S0EUS.\nWashington Railway and Electric pfd.,\nSESS, S043, GOERS, S0wSs, S0@SIg.\nwashington Gas, 2@69%.\nIl Telephone of Pennsylvania, 2G%,\n106 96,\nMoergenthaler, 16@196%, 1@196%s, 3619612,\n2al196ly, 3@196%. 0@1%Y5, 10@196%s.\nCommercial National Bank, 10a152;.\nP'otomac Ins. 5.\nAfter call\u2014Washington Rallway pre\nfprred, 10%.\nColumbia Railroad 6 per cent, $3,600@\nGAS BONDS.\nBld. Asked.\nWash, Gas 4 S......-Nesessnees 87 1\nWash, Gas Cert. Fa rn 101 107\nRAILROAD BONDS.\nCap. Traction R. R. \u00a5s..... \u00abdig 112\nAnacostia Potomac 5's...... 99 100\nCol RR. 08.......... .Joisg\nColumbia R. R, o's... 16 108\n10735 108\nMetropolitan R. R.\nWash. Ry. Elec. 4